    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"And his brothers,\" (each) according to his families in the registration, according to their descent (properly their generations; vide for תּולדות on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 2:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), are (were) the head (the first) Jeiel and Zechariah, and Bela, ... the son of Joel,\" probably the Joel already mentioned in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 5:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". \"His (i.e., Beerah's) brothers\" are the families related to the family of Beerah, which were descended from the brothers of Joel. That they were not, however, properly \"brothers,\" is clear from the fact that Bela's descent is traced back to Joel as the third of the preceding members of his family; and the conclusion would be the same, even if this Joel be another than the one mentioned in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 5:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The singular suffix with למשׁפּחתיו is to be taken distributively or אישׁ may be supplied before it in thought; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 2:34",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 11:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The word ראשׁ, \"head,\" for the first-born, stands here before the name, as in ",
        "children": []
      },
